<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-51-0346 </DOCNO><TEXT>In developing countries the use of renewable energy to pump water presentsa promising alternative. In a desert area in the south of Egypt in whichextensive underground water deposits have been found, a wind-driven pumpinstallation was set up within the framework of a joint German-Egyptianresearch plan. It was based on a modern wind-energy-converter, in whichthe electrical transfer at energy replaces the usual mechanical connectionbetween wind rotor and pump.</TEXT></DOC>